OL,3,CSenior officer to face misconduct
OL,4,Cmeeting for Manchester Arena response
OL,6,FResponding to the decision Terry
OL,7,FWoods, GMP Deputy Chief Constable,
OL,8,Foffered an "unreserved apology" to the
OL,9,Ffamilies.
OL,11,F"We support the IOPC's direction to
OL,12,Fhold a misconduct meeting after a
OL,13,Fcomplaint about a serving senior
OL,14,Fofficer involved in the response to
OL,15,Fthe Manchester Arena attack. The
OL,16,Foutcome of this disciplinary will be
OL,17,Fmade public.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
